This paper discusses internet service discovery and network topology, which are topics related to computer networks and security. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses scanning techniques and data analysis, which are related to network infrastructure and data science, respectively. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are also likely categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a method for selecting prefixes of interest, which involves data processing and optimization, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the trade-offs between reducing scan traffic and missing hosts, which involves decision-making and optimization, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible category as well.
